text:
Mirror 9: First Floor Hallway (Where the Felix the Cat Clock Was, Near the Bookshelves)

Break the mirror and enter the hallway. This is one large square.
On the left wall, use the note from Mirror 8 to set the clocks. They should be set to 6:00, 2:30, and 12:30.
Turn left to follow the hall. Arrange the decorative plates based on the note as well. The one of the man should be turned three times until the head faces the left. One of the women should be turned once so the head faces the right. The center plate with the mother and baby will stay upright.
Turn left to follow the hall. Across from the hanging clothes, use the note to arrange the three windows. The two outer ones should be opened, while the middle one remains closed.
Go past the hanging clothes and turn left again to see the three candle holders. Light a candle and place it in the middle one.
Walk around the hall, following the sound of a baby crying, until a passage opens. Go inside to take the baby monitor.
Bring the baby monitor to the Parents' Room and turn it on.
Jot down the code coming through the monitor (50373).
